00:22:21,006 --> 00:22:23,299
You use the wrong code, it blows.

260
00:22:23,384 --> 00:22:25,301
- So we need to get you in...
- Wait, wait.

261
00:22:25,386 --> 00:22:26,970
"We." Who's we?
Who are you working with?

262
00:22:27,054 --> 00:22:28,930
That's none of your business.

263
00:22:29,014 --> 00:22:31,057
Let's just call our host The Corporation.

264
00:22:31,517 --> 00:22:34,519
All right? I'm sending along a pro

265
00:22:34,603 --> 00:22:37,897
who specializes in this type of situation.
Her name is Maggie Chang.

266
00:22:37,982 --> 00:22:39,023
A woman.

267
00:22:39,108 --> 00:22:41,317
That usually goes along
with the name Maggie, yeah.

268
00:22:41,402 --> 00:22:42,569
Forget it.

269
00:22:43,070 --> 00:22:44,988
She can handle herself.

270
00:22:45,072 --> 00:22:46,906
But let me be clear.

271
00:22:47,867 --> 00:22:50,535
If anything happens to her,
she gets a hangnail,

272
00:22:50,619 --> 00:22:52,245
she gets hurt, she gets roughed up,

273
00:22:52,329 --> 00:22:56,875
she doesn't come back in exactly
the same condition she went in,

274
00:22:56,959 --> 00:23:01,045
you and your little gang of psychotic mutts
will never be seen again.

275
00:23:02,590 --> 00:23:04,632
And that, I promise you.

276
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:08,011
I don't make a very good babysitter.

277
00:23:08,554 --> 00:23:09,971
(CHUCKLING)

278
00:23:12,016 --> 00:23:14,058
Don't sell yourself short.

279
00:23:22,276 --> 00:23:25,069
You're gonna make a very good babysitter.

280
00:23:26,280 --> 00:23:28,114
Be there at 7:00.

281
00:24:08,989 --> 00:24:11,199
Hey. I'm Maggie Chang.

282
00:24:11,283 --> 00:24:13,660
- You're Barney Ross?
- Yeah.

283
00:24:13,744 --> 00:24:15,662
Mr. Church told you about me?

284
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:17,580
Said you wanna tag along?

285
00:24:17,665 --> 00:24:19,791
Help, not tag along.

286
00:24:21,001 --> 00:24:22,168
Nice motorcycle.

287
00:24:24,046 --> 00:24:26,256
Where we're going is new.
We don't know what to expect.

288
00:24:26,340 --> 00:24:27,966
Is it custom?

289
00:24:30,511 --> 00:24:32,762
I think it's a mistake, you coming along.

290
00:24:33,681 --> 00:24:35,056
Build it yourself?

291
00:24:36,517 --> 00:24:39,435
Yeah, I built it myself.
Are you playing games with me, Maggie?

292
00:24:39,854 --> 00:24:43,731
No. Are you playing games with me?

293
00:24:44,358 --> 00:24:45,984
Church told me what you said.

294
00:24:46,068 --> 00:24:49,404
I'm combat proficient.
I don't need a babysitter.

295
00:24:52,658 --> 00:24:54,534
So, when do we leave?

296
00:24:54,910 --> 00:24:56,536
0500.

297
00:24:57,955 --> 00:24:59,581
Nice meeting you.

298
00:25:01,542 --> 00:25:02,959
(REVVING ENGINE)

299
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:18,141
(SIXTIES MUSIC PLAYING)

300
00:25:37,244 --> 00:25:38,244
(GUNNER CLEARS THROAT)

301
00:25:40,915 --> 00:25:42,498
She's into me.

302
00:25:42,583 --> 00:25:44,125
She hates you.

303
00:25:45,294 --> 00:25:46,628
(EXHALES LOUDLY)
Watch this.

304
00:25:50,591 --> 00:25:52,091
(GUNNER CLEARS THROAT)

305
00:25:54,261 --> 00:25:56,179
(CONTINUES CLEARING THROAT)

306
00:25:58,098 --> 00:25:59,265
(COUGHS)

307
00:26:04,229 --> 00:26:05,355
Um...

308
00:26:12,321 --> 00:26:13,404
(CHUCKLING)

309
00:26:17,576 --> 00:26:20,995
You know, if something happens to her,
it's coming back on us.

310
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:22,830
Did you ever think to ask me
for my opinion?

311
00:26:22,915 --> 00:26:27,168
I told you 10 times before, I didn't have a
choice, unless you don't mind going to jail.

312
00:26:27,252 --> 00:26:28,711
Yeah, well, Church intimidated you.

313
00:26:28,796 --> 00:26:29,879
- Really?
- Yeah.

314
00:26:29,964 --> 00:26:31,047
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

315
00:26:31,131 --> 00:26:33,758
Oh, is that the woman
you can never fully trust calling again?

316
00:26:33,842 --> 00:26:36,177
You know, I will stab you one day.

317
00:26:37,846 --> 00:26:38,972
Hey, baby.

318
00:26:39,890 --> 00:26:41,599
Yeah, of course I'm thinking about you.

319
00:26:42,768 --> 00:26:44,936
What else is there to think about?

320
00:26:45,562 --> 00:26:46,729
(SCOFFING)

321
00:26:47,022 --> 00:26:48,189
Hopeless.

322
00:26:54,738 --> 00:26:55,738
Hey.

323
00:26:56,865 --> 00:26:59,033
You were in the Army, right?

324
00:26:59,118 --> 00:27:00,243
I can tell.

325
00:27:01,203 --> 00:27:03,830
Yes, ma'am. Three years.

326
00:27:03,914 --> 00:27:05,832
Last tour was Afghanistan, Kunar Province.

327
00:27:06,792 --> 00:27:08,418
Didn't like it any more?

328
00:27:08,502 --> 00:27:11,254
Uh... Long story.

329
00:27:11,338 --> 00:27:14,674
- I would like to hear it.
- All right.

330
00:27:16,260 --> 00:27:19,637
I was trained as a sniper,
and an instructor, too,

331
00:27:19,722 --> 00:27:23,391
but I actually wanted to mix it up,
get in on the action.

332
00:27:24,643 --> 00:27:27,520
Uh, this one time, we're stuck out
in this hell-hole valley.

333
00:27:28,147 --> 00:27:32,275
About 30 Taliban opened up
from these houses in the hills above us.

334
00:27:32,359 --> 00:27:34,444
And they got about eight of us
pinned down bad.

335
00:27:34,528 --> 00:27:38,406
So I called in for artillery support.
But, "No way," says the captain.

336
00:27:38,782 --> 00:27:40,783
Didn't wanna endanger the locals.

337
00:27:40,868 --> 00:27:46,456
So we scattered. Some crawled to a ditch,
some to the dry riverbed and the rest bailed.

338
00:27:46,540 --> 00:27:48,374
But we were still stuck in the kill zone.

339
00:27:49,668 --> 00:27:53,379
And we battled for,
I don't know, three hours.

340
00:27:55,382 --> 00:27:59,010
And finally, an Apache gunship chopper
showed up to provide air cover.

341
00:27:59,094 --> 00:28:00,928
Scattered the Hadjis, but...

342
00:28:04,391 --> 00:28:08,352
Smoke clears and four of my squad are dead
in the ditch and two in the riverbed.

343
00:28:15,402 --> 00:28:19,947
Yeah, I was mad and sick,
all dead for nothin'.

344
00:28:24,203 --> 00:28:27,371
You know the most screwed up thing of all

345
00:28:28,415 --> 00:28:29,749
is when I got back to base that night,

346
00:28:29,833 --> 00:28:34,253
I found out that they had shot
this stray dog that I adopted.

347
00:28:35,255 --> 00:28:38,424
Commander's orders to get rid
of all animals on the base.

348
00:28:40,010 --> 00:28:43,096
I mean, you'd think we had enough damn
shooting for one day, you know?

349
00:28:47,518 --> 00:28:50,478
And, anyway,
I figured it was time to move on.

350
00:28:51,271 --> 00:28:55,108
I heard these guys were looking
for someone, and here I am.

351
00:29:11,834 --> 00:29:13,084
You got that transponder?

352
00:29:13,168 --> 00:29:17,046
- Yes. Apparently, 15 kilometers northwest.
- Okay.

353
00:29:28,684 --> 00:29:30,143
(CHRISTMAS' CELL PHONE RINGING)

354
00:29:30,352 --> 00:29:31,978
Hello, darlin'.

355
00:29:32,855 --> 00:29:35,231
CHRISTMAS: Hello, darlin'.
I'm a little busy. Can I...

356
00:29:35,315 --> 00:29:37,150
Let's move. We're in and out of here fast.

357
00:29:37,234 --> 00:29:38,317
HALE: The sooner, the better.

358
00:29:38,402 --> 00:29:40,611
- Billy the Kid.
- Yeah?

359
00:29:40,696 --> 00:29:43,489
Today's your lucky day.
You get to take point.

360
00:29:43,866 --> 00:29:45,783
My pleasure, sir.

361
00:29:53,500 --> 00:29:54,667
Impressive.

362
00:29:57,421 --> 00:29:58,671
Hold on.

363
00:30:02,467 --> 00:30:03,718
Remember when you could do that?

364
00:30:03,802 --> 00:30:05,178
No, do you?

365
00:30:05,637 --> 00:30:06,846
I could blow him away if I needed to.

366
00:30:06,930 --> 00:30:08,890
Really? Look down.

367
00:30:11,143 --> 00:30:12,935
Look down. You see what I see?

368
00:30:13,020 --> 00:30:14,270
Short legs.

369
00:30:14,354 --> 00:30:17,607
1 ,000 bucks you can't catch him.
Go on, Flash.

370
00:30:18,859 --> 00:30:20,067
I'm a little busy.

371
00:30:20,152 --> 00:30:21,485
Are you?

372
00:30:37,628 --> 00:30:40,630
BILLY: (ON RADIO) Found the wreck
at the bottom of the hill, sir.

373
00:30:41,423 --> 00:30:43,633
Slow it down, Billy.
You're making us look bad.

374
00:30:43,717 --> 00:30:46,177
- BILLY: Say it again, over?
- You heard.

375
00:30:47,012 --> 00:30:51,057
- BILLY: Roger that. Slowing it down.
- (CHUCKLES) We appreciate it.

376
00:31:00,067 --> 00:31:02,151
Rest of the plane's over the hill, sir.

377
00:31:02,236 --> 00:31:03,861
Good work, Billy.

378
00:31:13,622 --> 00:31:16,457
HALE: Looks like somebody had a bad day.

379
00:31:18,669 --> 00:31:20,753
You guys go to the right.

380
00:31:22,589 --> 00:31:23,673
(GROWLING)

381
00:31:25,217 --> 00:31:26,467
- (GUNSHOTS)
- (WHIMPERING)

382
00:31:27,427 --> 00:31:29,387
BARNEY: Take off, Rover.

383
00:31:33,016 --> 00:31:36,560
All right, Billy.
You get a vantage point up there.

384
00:31:40,274 --> 00:31:41,857
Ask him.

385
00:31:41,942 --> 00:31:43,234
What you doing, Gunner?

386
00:31:43,318 --> 00:31:46,279
I'm making a bomb. You mind?

387
00:31:48,490 --> 00:31:51,367
- A maniac with brains.
- Scary.

388
00:31:51,785 --> 00:31:54,996
Phosphate rock, it's got a density of 1 .852.

389
00:31:55,080 --> 00:31:57,039
Melting point, 44.2 centigrade.

390
00:31:57,124 --> 00:31:59,750
Guys, I want some gunpowder, fast.

391
00:31:59,835 --> 00:32:02,169
Do it. The man's a chemical engineer, right?

392
00:32:02,254 --> 00:32:05,339
And a Fulbright Scholar. Pour it in the pipe.

393
00:32:06,591 --> 00:32:08,300
There's fur in their hands.

394
00:32:08,802 --> 00:32:09,885
These guys were alive

395
00:32:09,970 --> 00:32:11,262
- until the wolves got to them.
- (WOLF HOWLING)

396
00:32:11,722 --> 00:32:13,139
Be careful.

397
00:32:15,308 --> 00:32:16,934
(HOWLING GETTING LOUDER)

398
00:32:33,201 --> 00:32:34,660
Is this it?

399
00:32:38,749 --> 00:32:40,082
Yes, it's here.

400
00:32:42,085 --> 00:32:44,170
BARNEY: Caesar! I need you in here.

401
00:32:49,968 --> 00:32:52,553
Caesar, grab a hold of this thing.
I think it's spring-loaded.

402
00:32:52,637 --> 00:32:54,138
Lee, hook it on.

403
00:32:54,514 --> 00:32:56,474
Now, on the count of three, let's pull it back.

404
00:32:57,100 --> 00:32:58,184
Ready?

405
00:33:00,604 --> 00:33:03,022
One, two, three.

406
00:33:03,190 --> 00:33:04,565
(GRUNTING)

407
00:33:08,528 --> 00:33:10,821
- We can't hold this.
- You have to.

408
00:33:10,906 --> 00:33:12,406
(MEN STRAINING)

409
00:33:19,664 --> 00:33:21,123
(GROANING)

410
00:33:22,459 --> 00:33:23,542
BARNEY: Come on, Maggie!

411
00:33:25,754 --> 00:33:27,963
- Something's wrong.
- BARNEY: What?

412
00:33:28,048 --> 00:33:29,298
The explosive timer's triggered.

413
00:33:29,382 --> 00:33:30,966
- How long?
- Fifty-four seconds!

414
00:33:31,051 --> 00:33:32,343
If we leave now, we'll make it.

415
00:33:32,427 --> 00:33:34,637
- Maggie, let it go!
- No, I can do it!

416
00:33:36,807 --> 00:33:38,182
- BARNEY: Come on, Maggie!
- (GRUNTING)

417
00:33:38,266 --> 00:33:39,308
Maggie, what's going on?

418
00:33:40,435 --> 00:33:42,103
She tripped the detonator. Stay back!

419
00:33:48,401 --> 00:33:50,152
I'm losing my grip!

420
00:33:52,072 --> 00:33:54,031
You do, she's cut in half.

421
00:33:58,203 --> 00:33:59,578
- Come on, Maggie!
- Got it!

422
00:34:01,248 --> 00:34:02,706
(ALL PANTING)

423
00:34:04,835 --> 00:34:06,752
Yeah, lucky I was here.

424
00:34:06,837 --> 00:34:08,003
Just thinking that.

425
00:34:08,088 --> 00:34:10,881
I'm sorry. It's important I get this.

426
00:34:10,966 --> 00:34:13,551
You've got guts. No common sense.

427
00:34:13,635 --> 00:34:15,845
But guts. Come on.

428
00:34:16,429 --> 00:34:18,764
It's all right. We got it. Let's go.

429
00:34:18,849 --> 00:34:20,516
You're strong.

430
00:34:21,268 --> 00:34:23,936
Billy, come on down. We're out of here.

431
00:34:24,855 --> 00:34:25,980
GUNNER: What happened?

432
00:34:26,064 --> 00:34:28,816
HALE: That woman is crazy,
but I got a good pump.

433
00:34:35,615 --> 00:34:37,658
CHRISTMAS: Aren't you curious
about what's inside the case?

434
00:34:37,742 --> 00:34:40,202
No, I just wanna get Church off our back.

435
00:34:40,287 --> 00:34:41,871
Billy the Kid!

436
00:34:42,372 --> 00:34:44,540
Where the hell is he? Billy!

437
00:34:45,041 --> 00:34:46,125
(GUNS COCKING)

438
00:34:49,838 --> 00:34:51,046
VILAIN: Drop your weapons!

439
00:34:51,506 --> 00:34:52,506
TOLL: No way.

440
00:34:53,466 --> 00:34:54,633
It ain't happening.

441
00:34:55,927 --> 00:34:56,969
No?

442
00:35:00,307 --> 00:35:01,557
Are you sure?

443
00:35:08,523 --> 00:35:10,900
I'm sorry, sir. They were waitin'.

444
00:35:10,984 --> 00:35:13,235
- Drop the weapons now.
- Don't do it.

445
00:35:15,071 --> 00:35:16,155
(COCKING GUN)

446
00:35:18,074 --> 00:35:19,909
He's a strong soldier.

447
00:35:20,410 --> 00:35:22,411
Let's see how strong he is.

448
00:35:23,872 --> 00:35:24,997
Do it.

449
00:35:31,171 --> 00:35:32,421
- No!
- Oh.

450
00:35:34,341 --> 00:35:35,466
(MUFFLED GROAN)

451
00:35:41,681 --> 00:35:43,766
Don't do nothin' he says!
(GROANS)

452
00:35:47,395 --> 00:35:48,562
Don't talk.

453
00:35:49,356 --> 00:35:51,273
You should not speak.

454
00:35:51,358 --> 00:35:52,524
I'm gonna kill him.

455
00:35:53,026 --> 00:35:56,862
When I fire, his head will be gone.

456
00:35:58,448 --> 00:35:59,698
Three seconds.

457
00:36:00,116 --> 00:36:02,284
Don't give your weapons.
You don't owe me anything!

458
00:36:02,369 --> 00:36:03,369
VILAIN: One.

459
00:36:05,372 --> 00:36:06,372
Two.

460
00:36:08,875 --> 00:36:10,584
Don't do this! They'll kill everyone!

461
00:36:11,378 --> 00:36:12,461
He's gonna kill him.

462
00:36:14,965 --> 00:36:16,131
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

463
00:36:23,723 --> 00:36:25,099
Drop them!

464
00:36:25,892 --> 00:36:27,017
(GROANING)

465
00:36:27,352 --> 00:36:30,688
I'm impressed.
Very good use of intelligence.

466
00:36:33,191 --> 00:36:36,902
Everybody stay calm, we'll be done soon
and then we'll be on our way.

467
00:36:44,327 --> 00:36:46,078
Bring me that knife.

468
00:36:51,501 --> 00:36:53,168
What's this symbol?

469
00:36:54,462 --> 00:36:56,297
I like symbol.

470
00:37:00,552 --> 00:37:02,845
This is the symbol of the goat.

471
00:37:04,306 --> 00:37:06,765
The pet of Satan,

472
00:37:09,227 --> 00:37:10,519
they say.

473
00:37:12,689 --> 00:37:16,150
- You have a case that belongs to me.
- Does it?

474
00:37:16,234 --> 00:37:18,152
Yes, like your lives.

475
00:37:18,236 --> 00:37:20,529
It was lost. He doesn't have it.

476
00:37:21,197 --> 00:37:24,783
Last time, the case, or you will force me

477
00:37:28,330 --> 00:37:29,455
to cut

478
00:37:31,041 --> 00:37:33,042
his heart out.

479
00:37:34,627 --> 00:37:36,795
Do it, you piece of shit.

480
00:37:38,631 --> 00:37:39,965
Wait!

481
00:37:40,925 --> 00:37:41,967
(GROANS)

482
00:37:44,512 --> 00:37:45,512
Let me have it.

483
00:38:02,655 --> 00:38:03,822
Hey.

484
00:38:07,494 --> 00:38:08,494
You talking to me?

485
00:38:08,995 --> 00:38:10,496
Pick it up.

486
00:38:10,580 --> 00:38:12,790
- Hand it to me.
- Go get it yourself.

487
00:38:12,874 --> 00:38:14,083
- What was that?
- You heard.

488
00:38:21,299 --> 00:38:23,467
Now pick it up,

489
00:38:23,551 --> 00:38:25,761
hand it to me nicely,

490
00:38:25,845 --> 00:38:28,013
or you'll get what he got.

491
00:38:29,057 --> 00:38:30,516
Do it, Lee.

492
00:38:42,112 --> 00:38:44,196
You'll be all right, Billy.

493
00:38:51,621 --> 00:38:53,872
Respect is everything.

494
00:38:54,916 --> 00:38:57,459
Without respect, we're just people.

495
00:38:58,086 --> 00:38:59,962
Common, shitty people.

496
00:39:01,131 --> 00:39:02,506
I'm sorry, sir.

497
00:39:03,425 --> 00:39:05,467
It's not your fault.

498
00:39:09,139 --> 00:39:10,681
Now what?

499
00:39:11,433 --> 00:39:13,392
We're both fighting men.

500
00:39:14,519 --> 00:39:16,478
And I respect that.

501
00:39:16,855 --> 00:39:18,689
And fighting men,

502
00:39:18,773 --> 00:39:21,942
they don't deserve to be killed like sheep.

503
00:39:24,279 --> 00:39:25,446
But

504
00:39:29,951 --> 00:39:31,577
respect

505
00:39:32,245 --> 00:39:33,996
must be taught.

506
00:39:37,083 --> 00:39:40,878
Lie down with your face
on the ground until we leave.

507
00:39:44,757 --> 00:39:46,216
Don't challenge me.

508
00:39:47,594 --> 00:39:48,635
Get down.

509
00:39:55,768 --> 00:39:56,894
(HELICOPTER APPROACHING)

510
00:39:57,020 --> 00:39:58,061
Up.

511
00:40:10,116 --> 00:40:11,450
Are you afraid of me?

512
00:40:12,452 --> 00:40:14,495
No. I'm not.

513
00:40:17,457 --> 00:40:19,124
You should be.

514
00:40:42,941 --> 00:40:44,608
- I'm dying.
- Don't talk, Billy.

515
00:40:44,692 --> 00:40:46,193
Cut his hands loose!

516
00:40:46,277 --> 00:40:47,486
The letter.

517
00:41:10,343 --> 00:41:12,094
I'm so sorry.

518
00:41:12,178 --> 00:41:15,514
BARNEY: I believe you.

519
00:41:15,515 --> 00:41:17,057
What was in the case?

520
00:41:20,019 --> 00:41:22,521
A computer. Blueprint of a mine.

521
00:41:22,981 --> 00:41:26,441
A mine. What mine?

522
00:41:29,821 --> 00:41:34,032
The Russians stored nearly 5 tons
of weapons-grade plutonium.

523
00:41:34,117 --> 00:41:38,161
The mine was abandoned after the Cold War.
No one knows it's there.

524
00:41:38,246 --> 00:41:41,498
The blueprint shows
where the plutonium is stored.

525
00:41:42,292 --> 00:41:44,793
We want to stop it
before it gets in the wrong hands.

526
00:41:44,877 --> 00:41:46,920
I guess that didn't happen, did it?

527
00:41:48,798 --> 00:41:51,633
This kid died so some dirtbag
can make bombs.

528
00:41:55,430 --> 00:41:56,972
I'm so sorry.

529
00:41:58,057 --> 00:41:59,975
Not as sorry as I am.

530
00:42:04,814 --> 00:42:05,897
Let's take care of him.

531
00:42:12,155 --> 00:42:13,739
"Dear Sophia.

532
00:42:15,575 --> 00:42:19,536
"I wish I could find something different
to do besides just missing you,

533
00:42:19,620 --> 00:42:21,413
"but I can't.

534
00:42:21,497 --> 00:42:26,293
"The team's treating me good.
We got each other's backs.

535
00:42:28,129 --> 00:42:33,175
"I want you to know that wherever I end up,
I'll be wanting the very best for you.

536
00:42:34,010 --> 00:42:37,304
"And if some miracle happens,
and I come back again,

537
00:42:37,388 --> 00:42:40,390
"I hope I'm still your man. Much love, Billy."

538
00:42:43,519 --> 00:42:47,314
Why is it that
the one of us who wants to live the most,

539
00:42:47,398 --> 00:42:50,150
who deserves to live the most, dies?

540
00:42:50,234 --> 00:42:53,987
And the ones that deserve to die,
keep on living?

541
00:42:55,365 --> 00:42:57,532
What's the message in that?

542
00:42:59,035 --> 00:43:00,744
What's the plan?

543
00:43:01,704 --> 00:43:04,331
Track him, find him, kill him.

544
00:43:45,665 --> 00:43:48,708
RADIO DISPATCHER: CZ-1492, come on.
Requesting a response immediately.

545
00:43:48,793 --> 00:43:50,127
Who's this bozo?

546
00:43:50,628 --> 00:43:53,505
RADIO DISPATCHER: CZ-1492, this is
a secure air wave. Do you read?

547
00:43:54,090 --> 00:43:55,799
What's this about?

548
00:43:56,300 --> 00:43:58,218
MR. CHURCH: What's taking so long,
Barney Ross?

549
00:43:58,302 --> 00:44:01,763
This should have been a walk in the park
for you guys. Where's the case?

550
00:44:02,473 --> 00:44:03,682
Don't have it.

551
00:44:03,766 --> 00:44:07,352
I warned you what would happen
to you mutts if you pulled this shit again.

552
00:44:07,812 --> 00:44:10,188
A good man died trying to get that case.

553
00:44:11,315 --> 00:44:13,358
- I'm sorry about that.
- BARNEY: Are you?

554
00:44:13,443 --> 00:44:15,026
Yes, as a matter of fact, I am.

555
00:44:15,111 --> 00:44:18,196
But this sort of situation comes
with the territory, wouldn't you say?

556
00:44:18,281 --> 00:44:19,448
And so does payback.

557
00:44:21,951 --> 00:44:24,494
You know, Church, you're the kind of guy
that pulls the strings,

558
00:44:24,579 --> 00:44:26,037
and everyone else does your dirty work

559
00:44:26,122 --> 00:44:29,291
'cause you never had the guts
to do it yourself.

560
00:44:29,876 --> 00:44:31,001
We're done.

561
00:44:31,210 --> 00:44:32,210
(RADIO CUTS OUT)

562
00:44:58,613 --> 00:45:01,281
Sir, we got a problem.

563
00:45:01,365 --> 00:45:04,409
The digging has slowed down.
Too many are dying.

564
00:45:04,494 --> 00:45:05,577
They're exhausted.

565
00:45:07,163 --> 00:45:08,497
(MEN COUGHING)

566
00:45:12,376 --> 00:45:13,418
He's tired.

567
00:45:17,507 --> 00:45:19,216
Anybody else tired?

568
00:45:22,845 --> 00:45:24,095
Get more workers.

569
00:45:24,180 --> 00:45:26,598
We've already taken most
of the men from the villages.

570
00:45:26,682 --> 00:45:28,433
Get all the rest.

571
00:45:28,518 --> 00:45:30,936
Women, children, all of them.

572
00:45:44,784 --> 00:45:46,034
Show me.

573
00:45:51,165 --> 00:45:54,376
Now we know where it is. Right. Right.

574
00:45:55,211 --> 00:45:57,546
Okay. I know what to do.

575
00:45:57,630 --> 00:46:00,715
Good, I want the plutonium out
in three days.

576
00:46:02,760 --> 00:46:04,010
Three days?

577
00:46:04,095 --> 00:46:07,889
I have people ready
to pay four million a kilo now.

578
00:46:09,183 --> 00:46:10,809
Three days.

579
00:46:10,893 --> 00:46:11,935
No more.

580
00:46:12,770 --> 00:46:14,271
Understood.

581
00:46:15,273 --> 00:46:18,358
You're smart.
Imagine if 6 pounds of pure plutonium

582
00:46:18,442 --> 00:46:21,903
is powerful enough to change
the balance of the world.

583
00:46:23,197 --> 00:46:25,448
So, imagine what 5 tons would do.

584
00:46:25,533 --> 00:46:27,742
It's very interesting. Yeah?

585
00:46:37,128 --> 00:46:38,545
- Something's happening.
- What?

586
00:46:39,005 --> 00:46:40,964
The transmission stopped.
They're underground.

587
00:46:41,048 --> 00:46:43,049
Putting it down right here.

588
00:46:48,431 --> 00:46:51,558
BARNEY: Come on, let's hustle, hustle.
We gotta move.

589
00:46:52,602 --> 00:46:55,520
Christmas. Come on, Lee. Do you
even know what the hell you're doing?

590
00:46:55,605 --> 00:46:56,646
Five minutes.

591
00:46:56,731 --> 00:46:58,523
- Don't get your knickers in a twist.
- BARNEY: Right.

592
00:47:16,792 --> 00:47:18,960
BARNEY: Another transport truck.
Could be one of theirs.

593
00:47:19,420 --> 00:47:20,962
Let's check this place out.

594
00:47:24,967 --> 00:47:26,926
- (COCKING GUN)
- No shootin'.

595
00:47:27,011 --> 00:47:28,678
- Classics?
- Yeah.

596
00:47:30,806 --> 00:47:32,849
I've been dying to use these.

597
00:47:32,933 --> 00:47:34,309
We'll beat the truth out of them.

598
00:47:37,188 --> 00:47:39,022
Maggie, you tell the guys
to wait in the truck.

599
00:47:39,106 --> 00:47:40,398
Okay.

600
00:47:40,483 --> 00:47:42,942
- (LIVELY MUSIC PLAYING)
- (PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

601
00:47:53,663 --> 00:47:55,747
- They're here.
- Yeah.

602
00:48:08,260 --> 00:48:09,260
Speak English?

603
00:48:18,104 --> 00:48:19,938
- He's slightly gigantic.
- So?

604
00:48:20,022 --> 00:48:21,106
Just sayin'.

605
00:48:30,157 --> 00:48:32,409
- He's really gigantic.
- I said that.

606
00:48:33,160 --> 00:48:35,370
(SPEAKING BULGARIAN)

607
00:48:39,083 --> 00:48:40,083
Hey!

608
00:48:40,376 --> 00:48:41,543
- (GRUNTS)
- (WOMEN GASP)

609
00:48:45,923 --> 00:48:47,298
Can't beat a classic.

610
00:48:47,383 --> 00:48:49,759
I say we beat some info out of
these guys and get moving.

611
00:48:49,844 --> 00:48:50,927
Sounds good to me.

612
00:48:51,011 --> 00:48:52,053
Let's start with the midget.

613
00:48:52,138 --> 00:48:56,766
MAGGIE: Calm down, boys.
I can get them to talk with much less effort.

614
00:48:59,520 --> 00:49:02,397
What's she gonna do, give him a pedicure?

615
00:49:03,232 --> 00:49:04,816
(MAN GROANING)

616
00:49:05,317 --> 00:49:06,651
It's a little sick.

617
00:49:06,736 --> 00:49:08,111
Christmas, I need you to hotwire that truck

618
00:49:08,195 --> 00:49:10,405
and go back to the plane
and get the weapons.

619
00:49:10,489 --> 00:49:12,031
Why don't you get
one of those cheese-heads to do it?

620
00:49:12,116 --> 00:49:13,450
Stop complaining.

621
00:49:13,534 --> 00:49:15,285
CHRISTMAS: I should've bounced
one of these over your skull.

622
00:49:15,369 --> 00:49:16,995
- GUNNER: How'd it go?
- We're on. Let's move.

623
00:49:17,079 --> 00:49:18,705
TOLL: Cheese-heads.

624
00:49:23,377 --> 00:49:24,919
They call themselves Sangs.

625
00:49:25,004 --> 00:49:27,839
They say they control
everything east of the mountains.

626
00:49:27,923 --> 00:49:32,844
Robbery, kidnapping, assassinations.
Basically, a cartel for hire.

627
00:49:32,928 --> 00:49:34,345
How do you know the language?

628
00:49:34,430 --> 00:49:36,306
Easy. Put it together.

629
00:49:36,390 --> 00:49:39,851
It's a cross between
Ukraine and Bulgarian dialect.

630
00:49:39,935 --> 00:49:41,311
Impressed?

631
00:49:42,772 --> 00:49:43,897
A little.

632
00:49:45,316 --> 00:49:46,524
Christmas.

633
00:49:46,609 --> 00:49:48,610
- What?
- BARNEY: Why are you yellin'?

634
00:49:48,986 --> 00:49:51,196
'Cause you gave me the shit job, that's why.

635
00:49:51,280 --> 00:49:53,573
I'm gonna shoot you in the face
when I see ya.

636
00:49:53,657 --> 00:49:55,241
BARNEY: Where are you?

637
00:49:55,326 --> 00:49:57,368
The 60-year-old death trap you call a plane.

638
00:49:57,453 --> 00:49:59,037
Well, what's taking so long?

639
00:49:59,121 --> 00:50:00,705
Because there's bridges out, signs missing.

640
00:50:00,790 --> 00:50:03,166
I've been driving these dirt roads
for the last seven hours!

641
00:50:03,250 --> 00:50:04,459
You done complainin'?

642
00:50:04,794 --> 00:50:06,795
Thanks for the sympathy.

643
00:50:29,652 --> 00:50:30,693
This is weird.

644
00:50:33,572 --> 00:50:35,198
Just like home.

645
00:50:35,491 --> 00:50:36,491
That figures.

646
00:50:40,538 --> 00:50:41,746
What the hell is this place?

647
00:50:41,831 --> 00:50:44,415
MAGGIE: I believe
it's an old Soviet Army base.

648
00:50:44,917 --> 00:50:47,710
Probably used in the '80s. Cold War.

649
00:50:48,128 --> 00:50:52,006
They most likely staged maneuvers
and practice attacks against the U.S. here.

650
00:50:52,591 --> 00:50:55,510
Is there anything you don't know?

651
00:51:05,980 --> 00:51:08,940
HALE: Great. Just what I need.
50-year-old pizza.

652
00:51:14,613 --> 00:51:16,865
We'll bed down here for the night.

653
00:51:16,949 --> 00:51:18,783
(BLUES MUSIC PLAYING)

654
00:51:31,505 --> 00:51:32,714
Oh.

655
00:51:33,507 --> 00:51:35,884
This tastes like shit.

656
00:51:35,968 --> 00:51:36,968
How's yours?

657
00:51:37,887 --> 00:51:39,971
Can't complain about rigatoni.

658
00:51:40,681 --> 00:51:42,724
Plan ahead, fellas.

659
00:51:42,808 --> 00:51:44,601
That's all I have to say.

660
00:51:44,685 --> 00:51:47,896
Y'all, what if you knew
you were gonna die tomorrow?

661
00:51:47,980 --> 00:51:49,063
What would your last meal be?

662
00:51:49,690 --> 00:51:51,190
- One choice.
- One choice?

663
00:51:51,734 --> 00:51:53,151
It'd probably be cereal for you, huh?

664
00:51:53,235 --> 00:51:54,736
And what the hell's wrong with cereal?

665
00:51:54,820 --> 00:51:55,987
It's cliché.

666
00:51:56,405 --> 00:52:00,533
HALE: You gotta be original. You know,
if you were an original, broad-thinking man,

667
00:52:00,618 --> 00:52:03,661
you'd probably come up
with some special cereal, like Earios.

668
00:52:03,746 --> 00:52:06,456
You know, just like your ear.
You know, pour milk on them suckers,

669
00:52:06,540 --> 00:52:08,249
they just lay there and you don't hear shit.

670
00:52:08,584 --> 00:52:11,753
For the record, my hearing is 20/20.

671
00:52:13,213 --> 00:52:14,339
Barney?

672
00:52:14,924 --> 00:52:17,383
Donuts and most food that kills ya.

673
00:52:19,553 --> 00:52:20,595
That's deep, man.

674
00:52:20,679 --> 00:52:22,221
(CHUCKLING) You think so?

675
00:52:22,932 --> 00:52:23,932
Maggie?

676
00:52:24,600 --> 00:52:27,852
Crispy aromatic duck with plum sauce.

677
00:52:28,938 --> 00:52:30,313
Very sexy.

678
00:52:33,442 --> 00:52:34,776
But I like Italian, too.

679
00:52:37,696 --> 00:52:39,948
I'm starting to think Italian's overrated.

680
00:52:40,115 --> 00:52:41,658
(ALL LAUGHING)

681
00:52:45,204 --> 00:52:47,956
Hey. What about me?

682
00:52:51,627 --> 00:52:53,711
My favorite Swedish dinner would be

683
00:52:55,172 --> 00:52:57,840
baby seal and whale ass

684
00:53:00,177 --> 00:53:01,386
in the summer.

685
00:53:04,056 --> 00:53:08,434
But I'd really die for some Chinese.

686
00:53:13,983 --> 00:53:15,149
Then you're gonna starve to death.

687
00:53:15,234 --> 00:53:16,651
(ALL LAUGHING)

688
00:53:18,070 --> 00:53:19,445
All right, sweet dreams.

689
00:53:19,530 --> 00:53:21,114
Hey, Barney. I'm not done eatin', man.

690
00:53:45,431 --> 00:53:46,931
Can I ask you something?

691
00:53:47,725 --> 00:53:49,100
Sure, go ahead.

692
00:53:51,020 --> 00:53:53,146
Why are you so nervous around me?

693
00:53:54,940 --> 00:53:56,858
I don't get nervous, Maggie.

694
00:53:56,942 --> 00:53:58,818
What is it then?

695
00:53:59,445 --> 00:54:01,821
I just like keeping a distance.

696
00:54:02,865 --> 00:54:05,533
Is it because you don't want
to know any more people?

697
00:54:06,035 --> 00:54:09,787
Let's just say bad things have happened
to people I've gotten close to.

698
00:54:11,165 --> 00:54:13,541
Not a good way to live.

699
00:54:14,960 --> 00:54:16,711
I know.

700
00:54:18,464 --> 00:54:20,506
Do you think about
the young man who died?

701
00:54:22,468 --> 00:54:24,385
All the time.

702
00:54:25,220 --> 00:54:27,513
You don't talk about him much.

703
00:54:27,848 --> 00:54:30,224
No, that's how we deal with death.

704
00:54:31,351 --> 00:54:35,354
We can't change what it is,
so we keep it light until it's time to get dark.

705
00:54:35,439 --> 00:54:37,565
And then we get pitch black.

706
00:54:38,817 --> 00:54:40,068
Understand?

707
00:54:40,903 --> 00:54:42,278
I understand.

708
00:54:46,867 --> 00:54:48,367
Good night.

709
00:54:53,082 --> 00:54:54,665
Good night, Maggie.

710
00:55:01,090 --> 00:55:03,341
(UPBEAT MOTOWN PLAYING)

711
00:55:06,512 --> 00:55:08,429
(GUNNER SNORING LOUDLY)

712
00:55:19,817 --> 00:55:22,902
I swear to God, if he doesn't stop snoring,
I'm gonna shoot him.

713
00:55:24,863 --> 00:55:25,863
Gunner!

714
00:55:25,948 --> 00:55:27,281
(CHOKES MID-SNORE)

715
00:55:28,450 --> 00:55:29,450
You rang?

716
00:55:35,707 --> 00:55:37,208
I know it's a stupid question.

717
00:55:37,292 --> 00:55:39,585
I don't suppose you have
any more of that coffee.

718
00:55:39,670 --> 00:55:40,962
Pot only makes one cup.

719
00:55:41,046 --> 00:55:42,922
Yeah. That's what I figured.

720
00:55:44,258 --> 00:55:45,591
BARNEY: Listen up.

721
00:55:45,676 --> 00:55:48,719
Those guys said the congregation of Sangs
are probably in this area,

722
00:55:48,846 --> 00:55:50,304
concentrated east.

723
00:55:50,639 --> 00:55:52,390
So that's where we're going.

724
00:55:52,474 --> 00:55:53,975
We're out of here in 10 minutes.

725
00:55:54,059 --> 00:55:56,435
Get ready. Do what you gotta do.

726
00:56:02,401 --> 00:56:03,401
(SIGHS)

727
00:56:04,653 --> 00:56:05,862
(MEN TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

728
00:56:09,283 --> 00:56:11,325
Houston, we got a problem.

729
00:56:12,828 --> 00:56:13,953
- Down!
- (GUNFIRE)

730
00:56:16,415 --> 00:56:18,249
(LIVELY MOTOWN PLAYING LOUDLY)

731
00:56:25,257 --> 00:56:26,757
We gotta get out of here!

732
00:56:26,842 --> 00:56:29,177
- Go!
- HALE: Go, go, go!

733
00:56:29,261 --> 00:56:30,761
Go, go, go, go!

734
00:56:38,145 --> 00:56:39,145
Go.

735
00:56:47,821 --> 00:56:49,030
Save your ammo.

736
00:56:50,824 --> 00:56:52,408
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

737
00:56:53,202 --> 00:56:54,160
Where the hell are you?

738
00:56:54,244 --> 00:56:55,995
I'm almost there.

739
00:56:56,538 --> 00:56:57,914
Hey, what's going on? Are those shots?

740
00:56:59,333 --> 00:57:00,374
Yeah.

741
00:57:03,253 --> 00:57:05,171
- CHRISTMAS: What's happening?
- The Sangs got us pinned down.

742
00:57:05,255 --> 00:57:07,089
- Can you hold them off?
- Yeah, maybe with a tank.

743
00:57:08,717 --> 00:57:10,426
- Oh, shit.
- What?

744
00:57:12,721 --> 00:57:15,890
They got a tank.
Come on. Come on! Come on!

745
00:57:19,311 --> 00:57:20,394
Oh!

746
00:57:24,983 --> 00:57:26,567
Let's roll! Come on!

747
00:57:34,159 --> 00:57:35,451
I'm out.

748
00:57:36,662 --> 00:57:38,371
One left. Why not?

749
00:57:54,638 --> 00:57:56,222
Hey, who did that?

750
00:57:56,682 --> 00:57:58,266
Not me, I'm out.

751
00:58:08,610 --> 00:58:09,860
Hey, what just happened?

752
00:58:11,571 --> 00:58:13,072
Somebody got a little carried away.

753
00:58:13,448 --> 00:58:14,824
It looks that way.

754
00:58:14,908 --> 00:58:16,075
Where are the shooters?

755
00:58:16,618 --> 00:58:20,079
I don't know, but if they wanted us dead,
we'd be dead.

756
00:58:22,040 --> 00:58:23,249
Barney?

757
00:58:26,795 --> 00:58:28,713
(WESTERN MUSIC PLAYING)

758
00:58:38,807 --> 00:58:40,474
Don't freak out.

759
00:58:49,151 --> 00:58:50,651
Small world, huh, Barney?

760
00:58:51,153 --> 00:58:54,864
Booker? Rumor had it you were dead.

761
00:58:54,948 --> 00:58:58,242
Yeah, I heard that, too.
So, how's life treating ya?

762
00:58:58,327 --> 00:59:00,077
Been better.

763
00:59:00,162 --> 00:59:01,746
You did all this?

764
00:59:01,830 --> 00:59:03,998
I fly solo. I thought you knew that.

765
00:59:04,082 --> 00:59:05,791
Yeah, I heard it, but I didn't buy it.

766
00:59:06,251 --> 00:59:07,293
Well, now you do.

767
00:59:09,421 --> 00:59:10,504
This your team?

768
00:59:10,589 --> 00:59:14,800
Yeah. Gunner, Toll Road,
Hale Caesar and Maggie.

769
00:59:16,011 --> 00:59:19,430
Booker. You're the one
people call the Lone Wolf?

770
00:59:19,514 --> 00:59:22,516
I've been called that. But I have mellowed.

771
00:59:26,688 --> 00:59:28,105
Not that much.

772
00:59:29,524 --> 00:59:33,277
I heard another rumor,
that you were bitten by a king cobra?

773
00:59:33,362 --> 00:59:37,990
Yeah, I was.
But after five days of agonizing pain,

774
00:59:38,533 --> 00:59:40,242
the cobra died.

775
00:59:45,707 --> 00:59:47,124
(CHUCKLING)

776
00:59:48,418 --> 00:59:50,669
Hey, Booker. Great to see you, man.

777
00:59:51,046 --> 00:59:52,963
BOOKER: So, how'd you end up
in this godforsaken place?

778
00:59:53,048 --> 00:59:55,674
We got ambushed by Sangs
about 100 kilometers east of here,

779
00:59:55,759 --> 00:59:57,301
killed one of my men, young kid.

780
00:59:57,385 --> 00:59:59,303
- Yeah, sorry to hear that.
- Yeah.

781
00:59:59,387 --> 01:00:01,555
The Sangs are the lowest form of scum.

782
01:00:01,640 --> 01:00:03,182
Shooting them has been a good business.

783
01:00:03,266 --> 01:00:04,475
Do you know who the leader is?

784
01:00:04,559 --> 01:00:06,310
- Yeah, a guy named Vilain.
- Vilain.

785
01:00:06,394 --> 01:00:09,647
Mmm-hmm. Yeah, he pretty much controls
everything in this area.

786
01:00:09,731 --> 01:00:12,149
You're gonna need more men
if you expect to get out alive.

787
01:00:12,234 --> 01:00:13,651
Can you help out?

788
01:00:13,735 --> 01:00:16,070
Ah, sorry, Barney. I work alone.

789
01:00:16,154 --> 01:00:17,947
I understand. Thanks for showing up.

790
01:00:18,031 --> 01:00:19,615
My pleasure.

791
01:00:24,788 --> 01:00:25,788
Hey, Barney!

792
01:00:26,331 --> 01:00:27,998
There's a village down the road.

793
01:00:28,083 --> 01:00:30,543
They're good people,
and they hate the Sangs.

794
01:00:30,877 --> 01:00:33,337
- Maybe they can help out.
- Thanks.

795
01:00:33,421 --> 01:00:34,922
Happy hunting.

796
01:00:43,056 --> 01:00:44,098
What happened?

797
01:00:44,891 --> 01:00:46,016
I'm still alive.

798
01:00:46,101 --> 01:00:47,643
That's a matter of opinion. What'd I miss?

799
01:00:47,727 --> 01:00:50,729
I'll tell you about it on the way.
Come on, guys. Unload these weapons.

800
01:00:50,814 --> 01:00:53,399
Looks like Christmas
came way late this year.

801
01:00:53,483 --> 01:00:55,109
Yeah, I love you, too.

802
01:00:55,193 --> 01:00:56,777
Well, I'm happy to see you.

803
01:00:57,529 --> 01:00:59,572
Finally. Somebody with class.

804
01:01:05,287 --> 01:01:06,829
(SIXTIES MUSIC PLAYING)

805
01:01:07,164 --> 01:01:10,207
This has gotta be the town
that Booker was talking about.

806
01:01:10,292 --> 01:01:12,001
I could retire to a place like this.

807
01:01:15,172 --> 01:01:18,465
Clean air, no stress, raise some kids.

808
01:01:18,967 --> 01:01:20,885
You know, Maggie,
I could retire to a place like this.

809
01:01:20,969 --> 01:01:22,803
(LAUGHING)
You are so full of shit.

810
01:01:25,765 --> 01:01:26,849
(GUNSHOTS)

811
01:01:27,976 --> 01:01:29,310
BARNEY: Out, out, out!

812
01:01:35,400 --> 01:01:37,401
They're missing us by a mile.

813
01:01:38,987 --> 01:01:41,030
- PILAR: Put down guns.
- That's not happening.

814
01:01:41,948 --> 01:01:42,948
- (GUNSHOT)
- Whoa!

815
01:01:43,491 --> 01:01:45,159
The safest place is in front of their gun.

816
01:01:45,410 --> 01:01:47,453
- (LAUGHING)
- We will shoot you!

817
01:01:47,537 --> 01:01:49,830
No! Wait.

818
01:01:52,000 --> 01:01:55,336
These guys are here to help.
They want to help.

819
01:02:10,644 --> 01:02:12,937
Even you two rejects
could get lucky around here.

820
01:02:13,021 --> 01:02:14,438
- You think?
- I doubt it.

821
01:02:14,522 --> 01:02:15,648
Do you mind?

822
01:02:18,401 --> 01:02:19,610
Who you are?

823
01:02:19,694 --> 01:02:21,487
- We're Americans.
- Since when?

824
01:02:21,571 --> 01:02:22,613
Swedish.

825
01:02:22,697 --> 01:02:24,490
- Blackfoot.
- Chinese.

826
01:02:24,574 --> 01:02:26,659
- Retards.
- You done?

827
01:02:28,912 --> 01:02:30,454
What do you want?

828
01:02:31,122 --> 01:02:33,082
We're here to take care of the Sangs.

829
01:02:39,130 --> 01:02:41,257
Okay. Come inside.

830
01:02:43,969 --> 01:02:45,219
Come on.

831
01:02:47,013 --> 01:02:48,013
(GRUNTING)

832
01:02:54,896 --> 01:02:57,439
This is who we think you'd come for.

833
01:02:57,524 --> 01:02:58,774
This is who we will die for.

834
01:03:01,695 --> 01:03:05,072
First, they told us there'd be
good jobs, good money.

835
01:03:06,074 --> 01:03:08,450
Some went. But nobody come back.

836
01:03:09,494 --> 01:03:11,453
They come for more.

837
01:03:11,538 --> 01:03:14,581
They say as soon as our men go to job,

838
01:03:14,666 --> 01:03:16,834
the others come home.

839
01:03:18,128 --> 01:03:20,170
My husband goes.

840
01:03:20,672 --> 01:03:22,840
For a long time, we hear nothing.

841
01:03:25,218 --> 01:03:28,345
Then the Sangs come, and they take
all of the rest of the men.

842
01:03:28,430 --> 01:03:30,639
Forced them to work in the mines.

843
01:03:30,724 --> 01:03:33,225
Same in the next village. And the next.

844
01:03:33,768 --> 01:03:35,436
They take my sons.

845
01:03:36,021 --> 01:03:38,856
Now all that is left are the very young.

846
01:03:38,940 --> 01:03:41,442
And they will be back for them, too.
I know this.

847
01:03:41,526 --> 01:03:42,985
We all know this.

848
01:03:43,069 --> 01:03:45,612
So we hide them and we wait.

849
01:03:46,323 --> 01:03:48,532
Why don't you just move on? Leave.

850
01:03:48,616 --> 01:03:50,284
PILAR: This is our home.

851
01:03:50,368 --> 01:03:52,661
Our lives will be the last thing they take.

852
01:03:55,081 --> 01:03:56,707
Tell us why you're here now.

853
01:03:56,791 --> 01:03:58,667
We're tracking them.

854
01:03:59,294 --> 01:04:03,422
Can't you stay and help?
You saw the children!

855
01:04:04,049 --> 01:04:06,383
Soon they'll be done,
and they'll kill them all.

856
01:04:06,468 --> 01:04:08,302
We have our own business with them.

857
01:04:11,806 --> 01:04:14,433
I'm sorry. Let's go.

858
01:04:21,608 --> 01:04:22,816
(WOMAN SOBBING)

859
01:04:22,984 --> 01:04:24,568
I don't think
they're gonna last here much longer.

860
01:04:24,652 --> 01:04:26,195
I think they know that.

861
01:04:26,279 --> 01:04:28,197
So we're not gonna do anything about it?

862
01:04:28,281 --> 01:04:29,573
(SIGHING)

863
01:04:30,617 --> 01:04:32,201
I got an idea.

864
01:04:32,285 --> 01:04:34,286
And with your ego,
I think you're gonna love it.

865
01:04:34,371 --> 01:04:36,246
- My ego?
- Your ego.

866
01:04:36,331 --> 01:04:39,083
- What do you mean, my ego?
- You've got a big ego.

867
01:04:39,167 --> 01:04:40,417
Well, check your ego out.

868
01:04:40,502 --> 01:04:43,504
Oh, please. Your ego is like
the size of a dinosaur. Huge.

869
01:04:45,382 --> 01:04:47,174
(MAN TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

870
01:04:53,515 --> 01:04:56,183
We have it. We found the plutonium.

871
01:04:56,518 --> 01:04:58,185
(VILLAGERS TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

872
01:04:59,729 --> 01:05:01,522
(TRUCK APPROACHING)

873
01:05:08,863 --> 01:05:11,407
(VILLAGERS SHOUTING)

874
01:05:13,701 --> 01:05:15,160
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

875
01:05:21,209 --> 01:05:22,584
(BELL RINGING)

876
01:05:28,425 --> 01:05:30,926
(MEN SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

877
01:05:33,304 --> 01:05:34,346
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

878
01:05:36,975 --> 01:05:37,975
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

879
01:05:45,608 --> 01:05:47,443
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

880
01:05:53,241 --> 01:05:54,992
(PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

881
01:05:55,076 --> 01:05:56,368
(DISTANT SCREAMING)

882
01:05:59,664 --> 01:06:01,498
(PRAYING SOFTLY)

883
01:06:08,298 --> 01:06:10,591
(SPEAKING BULGARIAN)

884
01:06:13,261 --> 01:06:17,514
CHRISTMAS: By the power vested in me,
I now pronounce you

885
01:06:19,267 --> 01:06:20,350
man and knife.

886
01:06:24,439 --> 01:06:25,856
(MEN GRUNTING)

887
01:06:38,119 --> 01:06:39,119
(GUNSHOT)

888
01:06:53,384 --> 01:06:55,469
(MEN GROANING)

889
01:07:01,392 --> 01:07:03,894
(GROANING)

890
01:07:32,882 --> 01:07:34,174
One more!

891
01:07:39,180 --> 01:07:40,806
Rest in pieces.

892
01:07:43,226 --> 01:07:44,935
(MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

893
01:07:49,566 --> 01:07:51,316
- This is the last one?
- Da.

894
01:07:51,859 --> 01:07:52,901
Good.

895
01:07:58,199 --> 01:08:00,367
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

896
01:08:01,035 --> 01:08:03,120
The chambers are cleared.

897
01:08:11,546 --> 01:08:15,632
No loose ends. You bury them all.

898
01:08:25,143 --> 01:08:28,645
BARNEY: I see about a dozen guards,
light weapons,

899
01:08:28,730 --> 01:08:30,439
a couple of badass .50 cals.

900
01:08:30,565 --> 01:08:31,857
CHRISTMAS: Worse.

901
01:08:31,941 --> 01:08:33,817
Anti-tank devices.

902
01:08:34,527 --> 01:08:37,738
There's no way our trucks will
get through that mine field.

903
01:08:37,822 --> 01:08:39,448
Look, I know this is a stupid question,

904
01:08:39,532 --> 01:08:42,659
but you got any ideas
that won't get us killed?

905
01:08:42,744 --> 01:08:44,745
I got a few I'm thinking about.

906
01:09:00,428 --> 01:09:01,928
(PLANE APPROACHING)

907
01:09:11,898 --> 01:09:13,523
(ALL CLAMORING)

908
01:09:20,323 --> 01:09:22,282
- Boom time?
- Boom time.

909
01:09:35,963 --> 01:09:36,963
BARNEY: Target in sight!

910
01:09:38,299 --> 01:09:40,175
- Baby wants to travel!
- BARNEY: Fire!

911
01:09:42,970 --> 01:09:44,429
- Rock and roll!
- Fire!

912
01:09:46,933 --> 01:09:48,141
Bombs away!

913
01:09:51,020 --> 01:09:52,479
(GUARD SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

914
01:09:56,317 --> 01:09:57,317
Tighten up!

915
01:09:57,402 --> 01:09:59,569
- What's happening now?
- Chaos!

916
01:10:01,155 --> 01:10:03,407
- You're not doing what I think you're doing.
- Yeah, I am.

917
01:10:03,491 --> 01:10:04,658
Let's do it!

918
01:10:08,871 --> 01:10:10,122
Come on, let's move!

919
01:10:27,056 --> 01:10:28,056
(GRUNTING)

920
01:10:34,439 --> 01:10:35,731
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

921
01:10:36,107 --> 01:10:37,691
You're gonna need a new plane.

922
01:10:38,651 --> 01:10:40,068
(GUNS COCKING)

923
01:10:44,240 --> 01:10:46,366
(SPEAKING BULGARIAN)

924
01:10:47,243 --> 01:10:48,326
(BARNEY WHISTLES)

925
01:10:58,629 --> 01:10:59,963
- We're too late!
- What?

926
01:11:00,047 --> 01:11:01,465
The plutonium's gone.

927
01:11:04,552 --> 01:11:05,719
(MUFFLED EXPLOSIONS)

928
01:11:06,179 --> 01:11:07,179
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

929
01:11:08,181 --> 01:11:11,183
Come on, come on, let's get out of here!
Move, move! Come on!

930
01:11:11,434 --> 01:11:12,642
- (CLAMORING)
- Go, go, go!

931
01:11:12,727 --> 01:11:14,311
Move it, move it, move it!

932
01:11:14,395 --> 01:11:15,562
CHRISTMAS: Go, go, go!

933
01:11:16,189 --> 01:11:17,564
Go on, get out of here!

934
01:11:17,648 --> 01:11:19,232
Go, go, go, go!

935
01:11:22,069 --> 01:11:23,695
Pick it up! Pick it up!

936
01:11:30,870 --> 01:11:32,621
(PEOPLE COUGHING)

937
01:11:41,172 --> 01:11:43,089
We're gonna be here awhile.

938
01:11:43,299 --> 01:11:44,883
Oh, this is embarrassing.

939
01:11:44,967 --> 01:11:46,092
Yeah, it sure is.

940
01:11:46,636 --> 01:11:48,136
CHRISTMAS: What's he doing here?

941
01:11:48,221 --> 01:11:50,180
Saving this Chinese billionaire.

942
01:11:50,264 --> 01:11:53,225
Oh, yeah? That's funny. So are we.

943
01:11:53,309 --> 01:11:55,852
Well, then we have a scheduling problem,
don't we?

944
01:11:56,479 --> 01:11:58,396
Cut me loose, Frankenstein.

945
01:11:58,481 --> 01:11:59,606
BARNEY: Don't get nuts, Gunner.

946
01:12:00,233 --> 01:12:01,566
Do it.

947
01:12:01,651 --> 01:12:02,651
(GRUMBLES)

948
01:12:03,653 --> 01:12:05,362
- Where's your team?
- Waiting.

949
01:12:05,738 --> 01:12:08,240
I need a weapon. Something big.

950
01:12:08,324 --> 01:12:10,659
- Yours.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

951
01:12:10,743 --> 01:12:13,119
My big weapon's hangin' right where it is.

952
01:12:13,120 --> 01:12:14,871
(BLUES MUSIC PLAYING)

953
01:12:22,171 --> 01:12:24,047
Doesn't seem right.

954
01:12:24,131 --> 01:12:25,882
Going out this chickenshit way?

955
01:12:25,967 --> 01:12:27,092
Something like that.

956
01:12:27,718 --> 01:12:30,220
Hey, it ain't over yet, kids.

957
01:12:30,304 --> 01:12:31,888
I got a plan.

958
01:12:31,973 --> 01:12:33,557
Everybody calm down.

959
01:12:37,478 --> 01:12:38,687
Phosphate rock.

960
01:12:39,397 --> 01:12:40,605
What's he doing?

961
01:12:40,690 --> 01:12:42,315
Probably making a bomb.

962
01:12:42,650 --> 01:12:43,733
You serious?

963
01:12:44,235 --> 01:12:45,652
Not that much.

964
01:12:47,071 --> 01:12:50,824
I heard another rumor,
that you were bitten by a king cobra?

965
01:12:50,908 --> 01:12:55,537
Yeah, I was.
But after five days of agonizing pain,

966
01:12:56,080 --> 01:12:57,789
the cobra died.

967
01:13:03,254 --> 01:13:04,671
(CHUCKLING)

968
01:13:05,965 --> 01:13:08,216
Hey, Booker. Great to see you, man.

969
01:13:08,759 --> 01:13:10,343
Ask him.

970
01:13:10,428 --> 01:13:11,720
What you doing, Gunner?

971
01:13:11,804 --> 01:13:14,764
I'm making a bomb. You mind?

972
01:13:16,976 --> 01:13:19,853
- A maniac with brains.
- Scary.

973
01:13:20,271 --> 01:13:23,481
Phosphate rock, it's got a density of 1 .852.

974
01:13:23,566 --> 01:13:25,525
Melting point, 44.2 centigrade.

975
01:13:25,610 --> 01:13:28,236
Guys, I want some gunpowder, fast.

976
01:13:28,321 --> 01:13:30,655
Do it. The man's a chemical engineer, right?

977
01:13:30,740 --> 01:13:33,825
And a Fulbright Scholar. Pour it in the pipe.

978
01:13:34,493 --> 01:13:37,329
- The big man might be onto something.
- You think?

979
01:13:37,705 --> 01:13:39,372
Probably not.

980
01:13:39,457 --> 01:13:40,957
You need some help with that? Let's go!

981
01:13:41,042 --> 01:13:42,917
Here. Go blow yourself up.

982
01:13:43,002 --> 01:13:44,002
Lighter?

983
01:13:46,714 --> 01:13:48,006
I want that back.

984
01:13:48,633 --> 01:13:51,009
Better get back! This is gonna be loud!

985
01:13:51,093 --> 01:13:52,177
(GUNNER LAUGHING)

986
01:13:55,264 --> 01:13:56,598
Get back!

987
01:13:57,808 --> 01:13:58,808
Okay.

988
01:13:59,644 --> 01:14:01,269
All right, let's go!

989
01:14:02,021 --> 01:14:03,438
All right.

990
01:14:04,190 --> 01:14:07,317
Better turn around
unless you want your heads blown off.

991
01:14:07,401 --> 01:14:09,653
You better cover your ear.

992
01:14:10,321 --> 01:14:11,529
Come on.

993
01:14:21,791 --> 01:14:23,458
Well, the phosphorus must have been damp.

994
01:14:23,542 --> 01:14:24,542
Yeah, right.

995
01:14:24,627 --> 01:14:26,628
TOLL: Or you suck.
HALE: There's that.

996
01:14:26,712 --> 01:14:28,254
Don't cry, Gunner.

997
01:14:30,675 --> 01:14:32,509
BARNEY: You almost had an idea.

998
01:14:32,802 --> 01:14:34,302
(RUMBLING)

999
01:14:53,322 --> 01:14:55,240
(ROTORS POWERING DOWN)

1000
01:14:58,744 --> 01:15:00,412
I'm back.

1001
01:15:01,288 --> 01:15:03,164
How're you doin', Trench?

1002
01:15:03,499 --> 01:15:05,166
(ALL CLAMORING EXCITEDLY)

1003
01:15:08,754 --> 01:15:11,673
- Oh, I thank you. I thank you.
- You're welcome.

1004
01:15:16,470 --> 01:15:17,470
Bojan!

1005
01:15:17,972 --> 01:15:19,556
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

1006
01:15:27,565 --> 01:15:30,358
(LAUGHING AND WEEPING)

1007
01:15:35,948 --> 01:15:37,240
Hmm.

1008
01:15:43,372 --> 01:15:46,833
- We're even now, right?
- Right.

1009
01:15:46,917 --> 01:15:49,419
I'll be seeing you around, Trench.
Thanks a lot.

1010
01:15:49,503 --> 01:15:52,756
- Relax. It's not over yet.
- What?

1011
01:15:52,840 --> 01:15:54,591
That's right.

1012
01:15:59,013 --> 01:16:00,013
(CHUCKLING)

1013
01:16:00,973 --> 01:16:03,016
- How ya doin', pal?
- I was doing pretty good, Church.

1014
01:16:03,100 --> 01:16:04,100
What are you doing here?

1015
01:16:04,185 --> 01:16:07,270
- I heard there was a party in town.
- Yeah, but it's my party.

1016
01:16:07,354 --> 01:16:09,981
- Has he always been this selfish?
- Always.

1017
01:16:10,065 --> 01:16:11,274
Thanks.

1018
01:16:11,358 --> 01:16:12,609
(HELICOPTER APPROACHING)

1019
01:16:16,530 --> 01:16:19,365
You wanna kick Vilain's ass or not?

1020
01:16:19,450 --> 01:16:21,701
Don't forget the Little Rascals!

1021
01:16:44,767 --> 01:16:45,767
Move it.

1022
01:16:46,060 --> 01:16:47,477
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1023
01:17:22,763 --> 01:17:23,805
Move out!

1024
01:17:33,607 --> 01:17:36,192
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1025
01:17:40,030 --> 01:17:41,197
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1026
01:17:50,457 --> 01:17:53,710
Take the rest of the nukes to the hangar.
Now!

1027
01:17:53,794 --> 01:17:55,879
And get the plutonium on the plane.

1028
01:18:05,347 --> 01:18:06,431
Follow me.

1029
01:18:08,976 --> 01:18:10,393
We need to buy some time.

1030
01:18:17,902 --> 01:18:19,736
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1031
01:18:28,162 --> 01:18:29,162
(GUNSHOTS)

1032
01:18:34,752 --> 01:18:35,960
Go, go!

1033
01:18:47,556 --> 01:18:48,556
(GUNSHOT)

1034
01:18:49,850 --> 01:18:51,225
(WESTERN MUSIC PLAYS)

1035
01:18:57,566 --> 01:18:58,858
I'm out!

1036
01:19:08,243 --> 01:19:09,243
VILAIN: Hold them up!

1037
01:19:10,871 --> 01:19:13,081
Go! Go! Move!

1038
01:19:13,165 --> 01:19:14,165
Shit!

1039
01:19:34,228 --> 01:19:35,895
- Fun, huh?
- Yeah.

1040
01:19:35,980 --> 01:19:37,522
Oh, there he is!

1041
01:19:38,190 --> 01:19:39,232
Come on, Vilain.

1042
01:19:39,316 --> 01:19:40,858
- Let's go!
- Yeah.

1043
01:19:40,943 --> 01:19:42,485
Tear him apart!

1044
01:19:44,697 --> 01:19:46,072
(SCREAMING)

1045
01:20:00,713 --> 01:20:03,339
I'm almost out. I'll be back.

1046
01:20:03,424 --> 01:20:06,134
You've been back enough. I'll be back.

1047
01:20:07,052 --> 01:20:08,302
Yippee-ki-yay.

1048
01:20:14,393 --> 01:20:16,227
Who's next? Rambo?

1049
01:20:21,400 --> 01:20:22,442
Goodbye.

1050
01:20:23,068 --> 01:20:24,193
(SCREAMING)

1051
01:20:25,738 --> 01:20:26,696
Let's go.

1052
01:20:26,780 --> 01:20:27,905
(YELLING)

1053
01:20:30,325 --> 01:20:31,576
GUNNER: Maggots!

1054
01:20:47,760 --> 01:20:48,885
VILAIN: Start the engine!

1055
01:20:48,969 --> 01:20:51,012
Get that thing in the air.
I want to make some money!

1056
01:20:51,096 --> 01:20:52,096
HECTOR: Move!

1057
01:20:58,228 --> 01:20:59,854
Trench! Get in!

1058
01:21:03,942 --> 01:21:05,526
My shoe is bigger than this car.

1059
01:21:08,280 --> 01:21:09,614
Shoot something!

1060
01:21:10,491 --> 01:21:11,991
(TRENCH FIRING GUN)

1061
01:21:19,750 --> 01:21:20,750
MR. CHURCH: Come on.

1062
01:21:36,391 --> 01:21:37,767
(ALARM BEEPING)

1063
01:21:41,021 --> 01:21:44,649
Start the helicopter.
We have a special guest coming.

1064
01:21:46,568 --> 01:21:47,819
Let's go!

1065
01:21:48,320 --> 01:21:49,779
(MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

1066
01:21:51,532 --> 01:21:53,324
(MEN SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1067
01:22:04,545 --> 01:22:05,962
Take care of him!

1068
01:22:38,537 --> 01:22:39,787
This way!

1069
01:23:14,740 --> 01:23:15,740
(PROPELLER BUZZING)

1070
01:23:25,000 --> 01:23:26,417
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1071
01:23:27,252 --> 01:23:29,462
Cannot beat a classic.

1072
01:23:41,266 --> 01:23:42,391
(COCKING GUN)

1073
01:23:42,893 --> 01:23:44,602
- Barney!
- What are you doing here?

1074
01:23:49,107 --> 01:23:50,066
I'm going in there alone.

1075
01:23:50,150 --> 01:23:52,360
Don't follow me, no matter what,
do you understand?

1076
01:23:53,320 --> 01:23:55,321
- Do you understand?
- Yes.

1077
01:23:57,407 --> 01:24:01,869
That door opens up, and I don't come out,
and he does, you kill him.

1078
01:24:09,753 --> 01:24:11,879
VILAIN: Let's make it more dramatic.

1079
01:24:14,299 --> 01:24:15,424
Now, that's better.

1080
01:24:15,509 --> 01:24:16,926
(GUNSHOTS)

1081
01:24:31,316 --> 01:24:32,692
I'm out of bullets.

1082
01:24:32,776 --> 01:24:34,068
That's your problem.

1083
01:24:35,320 --> 01:24:36,821
VILAIN: Not really.

1084
01:24:43,662 --> 01:24:45,913
You wanna kill me like a man?

1085
01:24:49,167 --> 01:24:51,127
Or you wanna kill me

1086
01:24:54,673 --> 01:24:56,173
like a sheep?

1087
01:25:16,653 --> 01:25:17,695
Nice knife.

1088
01:25:33,211 --> 01:25:34,253
So.

1089
01:25:35,380 --> 01:25:36,589
What's it going to be?

1090
01:25:40,218 --> 01:25:42,595
Man or sheep?

1091
01:25:42,679 --> 01:25:44,388
You wanna man up?

1092
01:25:46,725 --> 01:25:48,059
I'll man you up.

1093
01:25:49,269 --> 01:25:50,269
(GASPS MOCKINGLY)

1094
01:26:01,865 --> 01:26:04,658
You must want to hurt me bad.

1095
01:26:05,118 --> 01:26:09,413
I'm not gonna hurt you.
I'm gonna take your life.

1096
01:26:12,250 --> 01:26:13,292
Come.

1097
01:26:35,357 --> 01:26:36,941
(GRUNTS)

1098
01:26:37,943 --> 01:26:39,527
Over so soon?

1099
01:26:39,945 --> 01:26:41,612
I want my money's worth.

1100
01:26:42,406 --> 01:26:44,407
- Come on, get up!
- Coming right up.

1101
01:26:46,743 --> 01:26:47,785
Going back down.

1102
01:27:00,799 --> 01:27:01,841
Taste good?

1103
01:27:02,884 --> 01:27:03,926
Talking to me?

1104
01:27:07,139 --> 01:27:08,222
(CHOKING)

1105
01:27:08,473 --> 01:27:09,682
Time to wrap this up.

1106
01:27:10,851 --> 01:27:12,351
(CHOKING)

1107
01:27:31,663 --> 01:27:32,830
(BARNEY GROANING)

1108
01:27:37,002 --> 01:27:40,337
Ironic. Here we are, you and I.

1109
01:27:41,339 --> 01:27:42,756
And your knife.

1110
01:27:44,801 --> 01:27:47,511
You're going to die. Like him.

1111
01:27:49,639 --> 01:27:50,639
What was his name?

1112
01:27:53,351 --> 01:27:55,269
What did you call him?

1113
01:27:58,190 --> 01:27:59,356
What does it matter?

1114
01:28:03,445 --> 01:28:05,446
Come on, Vilain.

1115
01:28:05,530 --> 01:28:07,615
Somebody's dying.

1116
01:28:07,699 --> 01:28:13,829
Come on, Vilain.

1117
01:28:14,873 --> 01:28:16,081
Come on!

1118
01:28:26,092 --> 01:28:27,092
(GROANS)

1119
01:28:39,731 --> 01:28:41,482
Get up, Vilain.

1120
01:28:45,987 --> 01:28:49,073
Get up.

1121
01:28:54,412 --> 01:28:56,288
Now turn around.

1122
01:28:57,249 --> 01:28:59,041
Turn around, sheep.

1123
01:29:03,004 --> 01:29:04,922
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1124
01:29:11,972 --> 01:29:13,013
Now what?

1125
01:29:13,265 --> 01:29:14,431
(YELLING)

1126
01:29:22,524 --> 01:29:24,441
His name was Billy.

1127
01:29:25,777 --> 01:29:26,944
(GROANS)

1128
01:29:45,255 --> 01:29:47,756
You know how to carve a turkey?

1129
01:29:49,134 --> 01:29:50,634
(SIRENS WAILING)

1130
01:29:54,973 --> 01:29:57,766
- You win?
- I think so.

1131
01:29:58,310 --> 01:29:59,560
Well, where's the proof?

1132
01:30:01,688 --> 01:30:02,980
Heads up.

1133
01:30:08,486 --> 01:30:09,612
Nice touch.

1134
01:30:10,071 --> 01:30:11,238
Mmm-hmm.

1135
01:30:12,115 --> 01:30:13,824
It is a nice touch.

1136
01:30:14,993 --> 01:30:17,328
A little extreme. But nice.

1137
01:30:17,412 --> 01:30:18,454
Mmm-hmm.

1138
01:30:21,333 --> 01:30:24,084
And as much as I hate to say this,
Bamm-Bamm,

1139
01:30:24,169 --> 01:30:26,587
now that we got control of the plutonium,

1140
01:30:26,671 --> 01:30:28,047
that makes us even.

1141
01:30:28,465 --> 01:30:29,673
Good.

1142
01:30:30,842 --> 01:30:33,677
So, Maggie, you'll be coming with us then?

1143
01:30:35,680 --> 01:30:37,222
When you're ready.

1144
01:30:43,688 --> 01:30:45,272
So I just want...

1145
01:30:52,697 --> 01:30:54,031
Wow.

1146
01:30:56,284 --> 01:30:58,619
They're okay, just a little immature.

1147
01:31:00,914 --> 01:31:05,125
I don't have to go.
If you want me to stay, I'll stay.

1148
01:31:07,671 --> 01:31:10,089
And I did save the babysitter's life.

1149
01:31:10,799 --> 01:31:12,424
That you did do.

1150
01:31:12,509 --> 01:31:14,468
Maybe I'm good luck for you.

1151
01:31:15,053 --> 01:31:18,514
But I could be bad luck for you,
and I can't allow that.

1152
01:31:22,102 --> 01:31:26,480
If you ever want help, call me,

1153
01:31:26,564 --> 01:31:27,815
or you're dead.

1154
01:31:28,358 --> 01:31:30,025
I'll do that.

1155
01:31:39,619 --> 01:31:40,869
What are you doing here?

1156
01:31:42,080 --> 01:31:44,915
Moving on. You killed all my business.

1157
01:31:44,999 --> 01:31:46,458
I thought you were the Lone Wolf.

1158
01:31:47,085 --> 01:31:48,335
(CHUCKLING SOFTLY)

1159
01:31:48,420 --> 01:31:50,671
Sometimes it's fun to run with the pack.

1160
01:31:50,755 --> 01:31:52,214
Sure, you got a point.

1161
01:31:52,298 --> 01:31:53,632
You take care, Maggie.

1162
01:32:01,558 --> 01:32:03,517
Oh, I almost forgot.

1163
01:32:03,601 --> 01:32:06,103
As a token of my gratitude,
my violent friend,

1164
01:32:06,187 --> 01:32:09,148
I got you and the Little Rascals a ride home.

1165
01:32:11,234 --> 01:32:12,901
- Behold.
- What?

1166
01:32:17,407 --> 01:32:18,782
Consider it a gift.

1167
01:32:21,077 --> 01:32:23,704
- That thing belongs in a museum.
- (CHUCKLING)

1168
01:32:23,788 --> 01:32:25,372
- We all do.
- (CHUCKLES)

1169
01:32:26,458 --> 01:32:29,126
- Hey, fun, right?
- Yeah, fun.

1170
01:32:30,712 --> 01:32:32,004
Take care.

1171
01:33:26,434 --> 01:33:29,895
(ALL CHANTING) Beware, beware,
walk with care.

1172
01:33:29,979 --> 01:33:31,939
Careful what you do.

1173
01:33:32,023 --> 01:33:34,858
Or Mumbo-Jumbo's gonna hoo-doo you.

1174
01:33:35,360 --> 01:33:37,569
Mumbo-Jumbo's gonna hoo-doo you.

1175
01:33:38,029 --> 01:33:41,323
Boomlay, boomlay, boomlay, boom!

1176
01:33:41,407 --> 01:33:42,574
To Billy!

1177
01:33:43,660 --> 01:33:45,494
- To Billy.
- ALL: To Billy.

1178
01:33:45,578 --> 01:33:47,037
GUNNER: Rest in peace.

1179
01:33:47,497 --> 01:33:49,957
- Man, I need a massage.
- Don't look at me.

1180
01:33:53,378 --> 01:33:56,255
- Hey.
- What?

1181
01:33:56,881 --> 01:33:59,925
- From one friend to another?
- What?

1182
01:34:00,718 --> 01:34:02,678
You really should learn how to fight.

1183
01:34:03,388 --> 01:34:05,097
(BOTH LAUGHING)

1184
01:34:07,767 --> 01:34:09,434
(UPBEAT ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)